The `Color` class is NOT associated with a color space.

As I have said, the API to follow is:
```js
color.convertSRGBToLinearSRGB();

color.copySRGBToLinearSRGB( source_color );
```
You need a source color space and a destination color space.

There are not that many variations, so hardwiring a separate method for each pair seems OK to me.

//

